Ask HN: What were the papers on the list Ilya Sutskever gave John Carmack?
text:
John Carmack's new interview on AI/AGI [1] carries a puzzle:

“So I asked Ilya Sutskever, OpenAI’s chief scientist, for a reading list. He gave me a list of like 40 research papers and said, ‘If you really learn all of these, you’ll know 90% of what matters today.’ And I did. I plowed through all those things and it all started sorting out in my head.”

What papers do you think were on this list?

[1] https://dallasinnovates.com/exclusive-qa-john-carmacks-different-path-to-artificial-general-intelligence/

text:
Howdy! I'm building out a curation service called Little Betsy (https://lilbetsy.com/). Little Betsy curates the margins of Etsy, finding unique and thoughtful creators worth your attention.

Right now I'm running an open application program for onboarding interesting sellers. There will be a cutoff for the entries but I'm not entirely sure yet when that will be.

Ask HN: Scammer Using Git as CDN – What to Do?
text:
I got an e-mail today buy someone using github as a CDN to phish passwords, pretending to be AMEX. He sent it to my "Batteries Plus" e-mail account.

Is there someone I can reach out to to shut this account down?

https://github.com/amxpdashbaord/summary/blob/main/header.js

It's a (poorly) obfuscated form whose POST goes here:

https://kbase.pratesis.com/php/init.php

or here:

https://dentalsline.com/wp-includes/ID3/id3.php

Thanks!
